The page linked out from Jira for "Text Formatting Notation Help" at [https://jira.atlassian.com/secure/WikiRendererHelpAction.jspa] should convey the update from a corresponding Bug Report, JRASERVER-9258, regarding how to escape a backlash using:
h4. Workaround

Insert the html escape sequence for the backslash character as:
{code:java}
&#92;{code}

h3. Problem Definition

The deletion of a custom field option may take a long time (and may even timeout) on instances with very large *customfieldvalue* tables.

When performing the deletion, a SELECT query is performed to identify the affected rows:
{code:sql}
SELECT ID, ISSUE, CUSTOMFIELD, UPDATED, PARENTKEY, STRINGVALUE, NUMBERVALUE, TEXTVALUE, DATEVALUE, VALUETYPE FROM public.customfieldvalue WHERE CUSTOMFIELD='<id>' AND STRINGVALUE='<id>' AND VALUETYPE IS NULL;
{code}
There is no covering index for this query predicate, resulting in an expensive sequential scan, e.g.:
{noformat}
jira=# explain analyze SELECT ID, ISSUE, CUSTOMFIELD, UPDATED, PARENTKEY, STRINGVALUE, NUMBERVALUE, TEXTVALUE, DATEVALUE, VALUETYPE FROM public.customfieldvalue WHERE CUSTOMFIELD='10300' AND STRINGVALUE='10111' AND VALUETYPE IS NULL;
                                                      QUERY PLAN
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Seq Scan on customfieldvalue  (cost=0.00..66574.70 rows=1 width=1218) (actual time=1994.961..1994.961 rows=0 loops=1)
   Filter: ((valuetype IS NULL) AND (customfield = '10300'::numeric) AND ((stringvalue)::text = '10111'::text))
   Rows Removed by Filter: 2081778
 Planning time: 9.137 ms
 Execution time: 1994.989 ms
(5 rows)
{noformat}
h3. Suggested Solution

Implement a new composite index on the *customfieldvalue* table on the _customfield_, _stringvalue_, and _valuetype_ columns. As a quick example:
{code:sql}
create index cfvalue_customfield_stringvalue_valuetype on customfieldvalue (customfield, stringvalue, valuetype);{code}
h3. Workaround
* If custom field option deletion is unacceptably slow, considering implementing the new index manually. The addition of new indexes can be expensive and should be discussed with your DBAs beforehand.
* In case of PSQL, setup an autovacuum.

h3. Issue Summary

When a Remote link_ is created with the REST API and an *application type* "com.atlassian.jira" is supplied and the relationship is _"relates to"_, then the Remote Link will not display on the issue page. We just get a spinner and _"Failed to load"_

!spin.png|thumbnail!

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create an input file with this JSON:
{noformat}
{

"application": {

"type": "com.atlassian.jira",

"name": "ACI SCRUM-8"

},

"relationship": "relates to",

"object": {

"url": "http://jira_remote:8087/browse/SCRUM-8",

"title": "SCRUM-8"

}

}
{noformat}
 # Create the remote link using the REST API
{noformat}
curl -H "X-ExperimentalApi: opt-in" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -u charlie:'charlie' -X POST "http://jira_local:8085/rest/api/2/issue/AL-13/remotelink" -d @input.json
{noformat}
# The response confirms the remote link as created:
{noformat}
{"id":10003,"self":"http://jira_local:8085/rest/api/2/issue/AL-13/remotelink/10003"}
{noformat}

h3. Expected Results
The remote link is rendered on the UI issue page on the local Jira

h3. Actual Results

!spin.png|thumbnail!

The below exception is thrown in the atlassian-jira.log file:
{noformat}
2020-06-16 06:21:35,047 https-jsse-nio-8443-exec-25 DEBUG jianue 381x73643x4 1lwew7u 10.5.232.251 /rest/viewIssue/1/remoteIssueLink/render/36202 [c.a.j.p.v.issuelink.rest.RemoteIssueLinkResource] Successfully retrieved the remote issue link '36202'
2020-06-16 06:21:35,047 https-jsse-nio-8443-exec-25 ERROR jianue 381x73643x4 1lwew7u 10.5.232.251 /rest/viewIssue/1/remoteIssueLink/render/36202 [c.a.j.p.v.issuelink.rest.RemoteIssueLinkResource] Error occurred while generating final HTML for remote issue link: java.lang.NullPointerException
{noformat}

No http request is sent to the remote Jira to fetch anything either.


h3. Workaround

Unless the application type is specifically needed, the _"type: com.atlassian.jira"_ line can simply be removed the JSON used to create the link and it will render just fine.

The [Creating a test environment for Jira|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver/creating-a-test-environment-for-jira-966063324.html] doc page should include the following to remove DVCS data from prod: 
{panel}
h3. 3. Remove DVCS Accounts:

By default the DVCS account info and secrets from your prod environment will be transferred over, this can cause confusion and performance issues in lower environments, to remove the data completely:
 # Delete the organization mapping from "AO_E8B6CC_ORGANIZATION_MAPPING":
{code:java}
delete from "AO_E8B6CC_ORGANIZATION_MAPPING"; {code}
 # Delete the repository mapping from "AO_E8B6CC_REPOSITORY_MAPPING":
{code:java}
delete from "AO_E8B6CC_REPOSITORY_MAPPING""{code}

 
{panel}
